## 3D plot, sphere

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))
ax3 = fig.add_subplot(projection='3d',computed_zorder=False)



u = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 100)
v = np.linspace(0, np.pi, 100)

x = 1 * np.outer(np.cos(u), np.sin(v))
y = 1 * np.outer(np.sin(u), np.sin(v))
z = 1 * np.outer(np.ones(np.size(u)), np.cos(v))

ax3.plot_surface(x, y, z,  rstride=4, cstride=4, color='k', linewidth=0, alpha=0.05)

theta_arr = np.linspace(0,2*np.pi,100)

xx_ = np.cos(theta_arr)
yy_ = np.sin(theta_arr)

ring = np.vstack((xx_,yy_,[0]*len(xx_)))

ax3.plot(*ring, color = 'k', alpha = 0.3, linewidth = 2)

# dots_red, = ax3.plot(*datar, color = 'r', alpha = 0.8, marker="o", linewidth = 0, markersize =2)



ax3.plot([-1.0,1.0],[0,0],[0,0], color = 'k', alpha = 0.5, linewidth = 2)
ax3.plot([0,0],[-1.0,1.0],[0,0], color = 'k', alpha = 0.5, linewidth = 2)
ax3.plot([0,0],[0,0],[-1.0,1.0], color = 'k', alpha = 1, linewidth = 2)

ax3.text(1.3,-0.1,0,  r"$|+\rangle$", size=8, zorder=1,  
    color='k')

    color='k')

    color='k')

ax3.set_box_aspect([1.0,1,0.95])
ax3.view_init(30, 20)

# Hide axes ticks

ax3.yaxis.pane.fill = False
ax3.zaxis.pane.fill = False

ax3.zaxis.pane.set_edgecolor('w')

## Take 2-photon tomography Measurement

anglesQWP=[0,0,45,45,45,45];
anglesLP = [0,90,45,-45,90,0];

N = len(anglesQWP);
# print(N)

f = IntProgress(min=0, max=N**2,style={'bar_color': 'maroon', 'description_width': 'initial'}\
                ,description='Measuring: ',layout=widgets.Layout(width='50%')) # instantiate the bar
display(f) # display the bar

anglePair = []
values = []

for i in range(N):

    ## Fill in rotations for one of the arms, QWP +LP 
    mountRotation_raw(IP_A,2,anglesQWP[i])
    mountRotation_raw(IP_A,1,anglesLP[i])

    for j in range(N):

        ## Fill in rotations for  one of the arms, QWP +LP 
        mountRotation_raw(IP_B,2,anglesQWP[j])
        mountRotation_raw(IP_B,1,anglesLP[j])
        
        time.sleep(0.5)
        
#         anglePair.append([anglesQWP[i], anglesLP[i], anglesQWP[j], anglesLP[j]])
        values.append(averageRates(IP_B,3))
#         print(j+(i)*N)
#         print(Basis[j+(i)*N])
        f.value += 1 # signal to increment the progress bar
#         print('Measuring: '+Basis[j+(i)*N])
        f.description = 'Measuring: '+Basis[j+(i)*N]
#         display(f)
        

values = np.array(values)
f.description = 'Done!'

mountRotation_raw(IP_A,2,anglesLP[0])

## Plotting the density matrices!

# if save_:
print('Do you want to save these files (Y/N)')
save_ = input()

if save_== 'Y' or save_=='y':
    save_ = True
elif save_== 'N' or save_=='n':
    save_ = False
else:
    print('Do you want to save these files (Y/N)')
    save_ = input()
    
if save_:
    print('Write a file name (no extension)')
    figTitle = input()

rhoLabels = ["HH", "HV",  "VH", "VV"]


fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
ax1 = fig.add_subplot(121)
ax2 = fig.add_subplot(122, projection='3d')


rho = rhoExtractFromData(values[:,2])

# print(np.real(rho))
# print(np.sign(rho.full()))
print(np.real(np.multiply(np.abs(rho.full()),np.sign(rho.full()))))
print(type(np.real(rho)))

p = qtp.visualization.hinton(rho, \
                            xlabels = rhoLabels, ylabels = rhoLabels, \
                            title = r"Re($\rho$), Top view ", cmap = cm.RdBu_r, ax = ax1)

_x = np.arange(4)
_y = np.arange(4)
_xx, _yy = np.meshgrid(_x, _y)
x, y = _xx.ravel(), _yy.ravel()

# top = np.real(rho.full()).ravel()
# top = np.abs(rho.full()).ravel()
top= np.real(np.multiply(np.abs(rho.full()),np.sign(rho.full()))).ravel()
bottom = np.zeros_like(top)
width = depth = 0.8


colors = plt.cm.RdBu_r((top/float(top.max()+0.1))*0.5+0.5)


alphas = np.power(abs(top)/float(top.max()),1)


for k in [ax2.xaxis,ax2.yaxis,ax2.zaxis]:
    k.set_pane_color((1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0))
    k._axinfo["grid"]['color'] =  (1,1,1,0)

ax2.set_xticks(np.array([0,1,2,3])+0.5)
ax2.set_xticklabels(['HH','HV','VH','VV'])
ax2.set_yticks(np.array([0,1,2,3])+0.5)
ax2.set_yticklabels(['HH','HV','VH','VV'])


for i in range(len(x)):
    ax2.bar3d(x[i],y[i],bottom[i], width, depth, top[i], alpha=1, color=colors[i], shade = False)
    ax2.bar3d(x[i],y[i],bottom[i], width, depth, top[i], alpha=0.2, color=colors[i], edgecolor = colors[i], linewidth = 1)
    



ax2.set_title('Metropolis plot')

ax2.xaxis.set_pane_color((1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0))
ax2.view_init(25, 15)
plt.gcf().set_dpi(300)
plt.show()

if save_:
    np.savetxt(figTitle+'.csv', np.real(rho), delimiter=",")
    fig.savefig(figTitle+'.png', dpi = 300)
    fig.savefig(figTitle+'.svg')
